The paper deals with feature extraction in hyperspectral imagery, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV). The proposed algorithm involves the calculation of eigenpairs, which is a common technique in machine learning (LG) and information theory (IT). The paper also discusses the complexity of the algorithm, which is a topic in numerical analysis (NA). Finally, the experiments involve both simulated data and real imagery, which could fall under the sub-category of signal processing (SI).
